---

<DocsLayout title="Kraft" sidebar={kraftSidebar} description="Build single-page applications in pure Kotlin with Kraft">

    <h1>Kraft</h1>

<p class="text-xl text-gray-400 !mt-2 !mb-8">
    A component-based framework for building single-page applications in Kotlin.
</p>

    <p>Kraft lets you build reactive web applications using <strong>only Kotlin</strong>. It compiles to JavaScript and
        uses <a href="https://preactjs.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Preact</a> (a 3KB React alternative) as its
        rendering engine — but you never touch Preact directly.</p>

    <p>You write components like this:</p>

<Code code={`class Counter(ctx: Ctx<Props>) : Component<Counter.Props>(ctx) {
    data class Props(val start: Int)

    private var count by value(props.start)

    override fun VDom.render() {
        div {
            h2 { +"Count: ${'$'}count" }
            ui.blue.button {
                onClick { count++ }
                +"Increment"
            }
        }
    }
}`} lang="kotlin" theme="vitesse-dark" />

    <Aside>We didn't set out to write a framework. We just wanted to write Kotlin in the browser and the existing
        wrappers didn't quite fit.
    </Aside>

    {sections.map(section => (
            <>
                <h2>{section.title}</h2>
                <div class="not-prose grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 my-6">
                    {section.items.map(item => (
                            <a href={item.href}
                               class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.02] hover:border-brand-400/40 transition-all">
